snippet.textDisplay:
One extremely interesting fact about all this is that in 1986 the UK government, under Margaret Thatcher, was a very influential and enthusiastic protagonist in securing the Single European Act (SEA), which was to set  a deadline of 1992 for the full completion of the single market.

The SEA (1986) involved the following: the removal of barriers to movement of people (Well, I never! 😳); the harmonisation of national standards; rules on how governments buy services and goods; the liberalisation of financial institutions; the setting of more standard value added tax rates, and European business laws.

All things which the UK government now conveniently forgets being instrumental in creating because it fits their narrative of trying to escape the obligations and responsibilities it agreed to with the EU.

Funny, that, don't you think?😏
